collectible.description: Before I tell you more, I wish you to know that the thing known as a cross was not brought to Africa by missionaries, knowledge of the cross in its many forms, was here in Africa from the remotest of remote times. Africans believed that the cross, either made of wood, ivory or metal was a powerful object, possessed of great magic, capable of unleashing powers of healing, or renewing or powers of destruction and killing.

With an accurate understanding of Klava and his Law 
They went about the work of building, 
A new Nation, 
The TinoVerse. 

Wise one who understood the law 
That was handed down from the gnomes of Long Ago 
Reflected the true meaning to his believers every day 
And they surrendered their discerning of it into his care 
And keeping 
For they trusted that he would lead in the right way

Epochs passed Wise one forged on 
Mining knowledge and protecting 
The Book of the Everlasting Now
